benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/bundles - Retrieve bundles for account

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC06, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC10, @TC12, @TC13, @TC15, @TC16, @TC18, @TC19, @TC20, @TC22, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover successful retrieval, filtering, audit parameters, no bundles, single bundle, invalid accountId, non-existent account, extra parameters, authorization, large data, concurrency, regression, backward compatibility, data consistency, input edge cases, and documentation validation.

Error Handling: @TC09, @TC10, @TC11, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC17, @TC21 cover invalid account IDs, non-existent accounts, unsupported parameters, service unavailability, authorization issues, timeout, and dependency failures.
Special Cases: @TC07, @TC08, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover no bundles, single bundle, empty filters, partial inputs, and documentation compliance.
gaps: Pagination: No tests explicitly verify handling of large datasets with pagination or limit/offset parameters.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios check for cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate rapid repeated requests to verify rate limiting or throttling.
Response Headers: No validation of headers beyond status codes and body content.
Concurrent Requests: While @TC18 mentions concurrency, it lacks detailed stress or load testing scenarios.
Retry Logic: No tests for retry mechanisms on transient failures.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for pagination to ensure large datasets are handled correctly and efficiently.
Include scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Implement rate limiting tests to confirm system stability under high request volumes.
Validate response headers for cache control, ETag, and other relevant metadata.
Enhance concurrency testing with load and stress scenarios to detect race conditions or data inconsistencies.
Create tests for retry logic and idempotency in case of transient failures.
